  "content": "The patient was diagnosed with type 2 diabetes mellitus and started on metformin 500mg twice daily. She also reports occasional headaches and dizziness. Previous medications include lisinopril for hypertension and atorvastatin for hyperlipidemia.\n\nPhysical examination reveals blood pressure of 138/88 mmHg and heart rate of 78 bpm. The patient appears well-nourished and in no acute distress. Cardiovascular exam shows regular rate and rhythm with no murmurs. Respiratory exam reveals clear lungs bilaterally.\n\nLaboratory results from last week show HbA1c of 7.8%, fasting glucose of 156 mg/dL, and total cholesterol of 245 mg/dL. Renal function tests are within normal limits with creatinine at 0.9 mg/dL.\n\nAssessment and Plan: The patient has poorly controlled type 2 diabetes mellitus. We will increase metformin to 1000mg twice daily and consider adding glipizide if glycemic targets are not met in three months. Continue lisinopril 10mg for hypertension management. Order repeat HbA1c in 3 months. The patient was counseled on diabetic diet and regular exercise. Follow up in 3 months or sooner if symptoms worsen.",
